title: Rewterz Threat Alert FormBook Malware Active IOCs

sentences: Since 2016, FormBook has been active as a data-stealing malware that affects 4% of enterprises in 2020. It tracks and monitors keystrokes, finds and accesses files, takes screenshots, harvests passwords from various browsers, drops files, downloads, and executes stealthier malware in response to orders from a command-and-control server (C2). The cybercriminals behind these email campaigns used a variety of distribution techniques to deliver this malware, including PDFs, Office Documents, ZIP, RAR, etc.
